          <LEXSenses>
            <LEXSense LanguageCode="en" LastEdited="2021-10-13 12:44:06" LastEditedBy="">
              <DefinitionLong/>
              <DefinitionShort>pertaining to sharing with someone else in a possession or a relationship implying mutual interest</DefinitionShort>
              <Glosses>
                <Gloss>shared</Gloss>
                <Gloss>mutual</Gloss>
                <Gloss>common</Gloss>
              </Glosses>
              <Comments>Since the emphasis in {S:05600100400010} is upon the fact that Paul and Titus have the same faith, one may also translate as ‘… the faith that you and I have’ or ‘… the faith we both believe in.’</Comments>
            </LEXSense>
